[SN]TITLE[SN]
Londonderry: Residents' health fears over fire at River Ridge Recycling site

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
People living near a major fire at a waste plant in Londonderry have expressed concerns about the possible impact on their health.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
12 November 2015 Last updated at 14:29 GMT
Several thousand tonnes of household waste is still burning, more than 24 hours after the fire started at the plant on the Electra Road in Campsie
BBC Newsline's Keiron Tourish reports.
